# Plan: Project-Local Database Query Skills

## Context
Create two Claude Code skills local to the `gpsl-cp-system` project so that `/neo4j-query` and `/postgres-query` invoke query-helper prompts pre-loaded with the actual schema of this codebase — making query assistance far more precise than a generic helper.

## Files to Create

- `C:\Users\mbrow\git\gpsl-cp-system\.claude\skills\neo4j-query.md`
- `C:\Users\mbrow\git\gpsl-cp-system\.claude\skills\postgres-query.md`

## What Each Skill Contains

### neo4j-query.md
- Role: you are a Cypher query expert for this specific graph
- Full node schema:
  - Document (sourceId, name, createdAt)
  - Text (sourceId, guid, pageNumber, paragraphNumber, text, nodeType, nodePath)
  - Collection (sourceId, name, createdAt)
  - GlossaryTerm (name, wordnv, acronym, posnv, tag, meaning, category, taxonomy_l1/l2/l3, id)
  - Terminology (sourceId, name)
  - Acronym (name, acronym, meaning, id)
  - Date, Requirement, Temporal (referenced, limited detail)
- Full relationship schema:
  - (Collection)-[:HAS_DOCUMENT]->(Document)
  - (Document)-[:HAS_TEXT]->(Text)
  - (Collection)-[:USES]->(Terminology)
  - (Text)-[:CONTAINS]->(GlossaryTerm)
  - (GlossaryTerm)-[:HAS_ACRONYM]->(Acronym)
  - (GlossaryTerm)-[:IS_PART_OF]->(Terminology)
  - (Acronym)-[:IS_PART_OF]->(Terminology)
- Key indexes (sourceId, guid, id are unique)
- Stack context: NestJS + neo4j-driver + nest-neo4j, queries live in `*.queries.ts` files
- Instructions: ask for missing context, suggest EXPLAIN/PROFILE when relevant, warn about full graph scans, prefer parameterized queries

### postgres-query.md
- Role: you are a PostgreSQL query expert for this specific schema
- Full table schema (all 10 tables with column names, types, constraints, indexes)
- FK relationships between tables
- Notable: text_chunks uses pgvector (vector(1536)) for embeddings
- Stack context: TypeORM + NestJS, entities in `discovery-database/src/entities/`, migrations in `discovery-database/src/migrations/`
- Instructions: ask for missing context, suggest EXPLAIN ANALYZE when relevant, warn about missing index usage, prefer parameterized queries, note TypeORM QueryBuilder vs raw SQL tradeoffs

## Invocation
User types `/neo4j-query` or `/postgres-query` to load the skill into the session.

